</ul></div></nav><div class="site-inner"><div class="content-sidebar-wrap"><main class="content" role="main" itemprop="mainContentOfPage" itemscope="itemscope" itemtype="http://schema.org/Blog"><article class="post-813 post type-post status-publish format-standard category-mains category-vegan category-vegetarian entry" itemscope="itemscope" itemtype="http://schema.org/BlogPosting" itemprop="blogPost"><header class="entry-header"><h1 class="entry-title" itemprop="headline">Quinoa, Black Bean, and Mango Salad</h1> 
<p class="entry-meta"><time class="entry-time" itemprop="datePublished" datetime="2015-05-18T20:00:44+00:00">May 18, 2015</time> by <span class="entry-author" itemprop="author" itemscope="itemscope" itemtype="http://schema.org/Person"><a href="http://sweetlittlekitchen.com/author/alexa/" class="entry-author-link" itemprop="url" rel="author"><span class="entry-author-name" itemprop="name">Alexa</span></a></span> <span class="entry-comments-link"><a href="http://sweetlittlekitchen.com/quinoa-black-bean-and-mango-salad/#comments">5 Comments</a></span> </p></header><div class="entry-content" itemprop="text"><p>I am pretty jet-lagged as I type this post, so please forgive any grammatical errors and nonsensical ramblings. But I will have you know that I had the most unusual and delicious dish at a cafe this afternoon &#8211; it was called &#8220;City Stew.&#8221; It consisted of brown rice topped with diced vegetable soup-esque ingredients, bound together with a sauce resembling Japanese curry, sans curry powder. The veggies (potatoes, celery, and carrots) were stewed with some apples, which added a little fruitiness. It was unlike anything I&#8217;ve ever had before, but it was wonderful, so I might try to re-create it on the blog some day. Have any of you encountered a dish like this before?</p>
<p>On another note, this Quinoa, Black Bean, and Mango Salad is a fantastic light entree or side. It&#8217;s sweet from the mango, has a little kick from the jalapeno, and is filling and protein-packed from the quinoa and black beans. It also packs really easily and you don&#8217;t have to re-heat it, so it&#8217;s a great lunch to take to work.</p>
<p><a href="http://sweetlittlekitchen.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/quinoa-black-bean-mango-salad.jpg">
